===message:One issue that I have is that we as a society, (no matter what country) send out double messages.  If a group or organization uses violence to atain their goals this is seen as a negative thing that brings about nothing good for anyone.  On the other hand when as a country, we have a dispute with another country and have tried to resolve issues or attain a goal through other means, we will fight.  Each of these movement used violent and nonviolent methods in order to make their points known and gain a sense of equality in terms of housing, education, employment, etc.  You are right, the violent methods probably did not work, but the question is why.  Why doesn't violence work in some situations, but is seen as the only solution in others?
